added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: Quarantine
added.description: After a chemical spill, the girls and Mojo find themselves trapped together.

added.title: Salamander
added.description: When the professor is kidnapped, the girls must go to a mysterious island to save him.

added.title: The Trouble With Bubbles
added.description: When Bubbles is overworked, she uses her coding skills to come up with a new solution.

added.title: Sugar, Spice, and Super Lice
added.description: When Buttercup gets super lice, her sisters must battle them to save her.

added.title: A Slight Hiccup
added.description: The Girls must overcome their supersonic hiccups to stop the Gnat's latest evil plan!

added.title: Derby Dollies
added.description: When Bubbles joins the Derbytantes, Buttercup finds herself on the sidelines.

added.title: Deb O'Nair
added.description: A classy queen of etiquette makes the Utoniums question their superhero way of life.

added.title: Aliver
added.description: The Girls compete for the title of World's Greatest Superheroes!

added.title: Him Diddle Riddle
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Slave the Day/Los Dos Mojos
added.description: Slave The Day: The girls save Big Billy's life, and he is forever indebted. But how will they get this bumbling fellow out of their way so they can save the world?/Los Dos Mojos: After she gets knocked on the head, Bubbles wakes up thinking she is Mojo Jojo. What is the world going to do with two evil Mojos?

added.title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
added.description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

added.title: The Eyes
added.description: One night, an exhausted Finn and Jake are creeped out by an odd-looking horse that mysteriously appears outside the treehouse and keeps them awake.  They try everything they can think of to get rid of the freaky horse, but nothing seems to work.  What does it want?  And why won't it just leave them alone?

added.title: The Other Tarts
added.description: Finn and Jake volunteer for a dangerous assignment: currying rare tarts for a meeting of Ooo royalty.

added.title: Her Parents
added.description: Jake pretends to be a rainicorn in order to make Lady's parents like him.

added.title: The Pods
added.description: Finn and Jake must sort out the good magic beans from the bad.

added.title: The Silent King
added.description: Finn and Jake get to live like royalty, but soon fine the easy life doesn't suit them. Or at least not Finn.

added.title: Business Time
added.description: Finn and Jake must travel to a far-off land to stop Jake from becoming permanently Lumpy.

added.title: My Two Favorite People
added.description: Jake tries to broker peace between Rainicorn and Finn.

added.title: The Witch's Garden
added.description: Jake loses his powers to a witch.

added.title: What is Life?
added.description: In his attempt to out-prank Jake, Finn inadvertently creates the Ice King's son.

added.title: Rainy Day Daydream
added.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.

added.title: Party Animal
added.description: Green Arrow, who is determined to finally throw a successful holiday party for the Justice League, finds his plans thwarted when Plastic Man brings a tranquilized super villain to the gathering.

removed.title: Not So Secret Service
removed.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

removed.title: Can't Buy Love
removed.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

removed.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
removed.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

removed.title: Musclecup
removed.description: Feeling inadequate as a superhero, Buttercup bulks up…to the max.

removed.title: Escape from Monster Island
removed.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

removed.title: Man Up
removed.description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

removed.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
removed.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

removed.title: Little Octi Lost
removed.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

removed.title: Blundercup
removed.description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

removed.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
removed.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

removed.title: A Star is Blossom
removed.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

removed.title: Trouble Clef
removed.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

removed.title: Imagine That
removed.description: The Girls have to battle Him after he causes Bubbles' imagination to run wild.

removed.title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
removed.description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.

removed.title: Abate and Switch
removed.description: When the JLA tries to stop the Brothers Djinn, the ghoulish trio are able to direct spells on our heroes by saying their names forcing them to disguise themselves as each other in order to foil the spells.

removed.title: Repulse!
removed.description: Luthor infects Superman with a magnetic charge that repels everything. As the repulsing charge grows, the Magnetized Man of Steel is fated to spend the rest of his life isolated in space unless the Justice League can figure out a way to free him.

removed.title: Galaxy Jest
removed.description: Joker is abducted into space by Mongul to entertain Mongul's troops. Unless the Justice League can re-capture him in time, a Joker gas bomb will go off in Gotham threatening the city.

removed.title: Under a Red Sun
removed.description: Steppenwolf "boom tubes" Superman to a planet with a red sun in order to make the Man of Steel powerless. Somehow Batman and Big Barda have to locate the planet before Superman is destroyed.

removed.title: Nuclear Family Values
removed.description: Firestorm encounters the Nuclear Family, a misguided group of robots who resemble a '50's sitcom family. They intend on blowing up a nuclear power plant in order to create a home where no one can touch them and they hope to use Firestorm's power to help them.

removed.title: Power Outage
removed.description: A ghoul known as Calythos possesses the Parasite in order to drain the Justice League of its powers and use that stolen strength to open a massive volcano.

removed.title: Freak City
removed.description: A magical man turns Finn into a foot. They meet others who have been similarly wronged and must work together.

removed.title: James II
removed.description: Finn and Jake discover that Clone James has been faking his own death to collect medals. But there are 25 Jameses running amok!

removed.title: Who Would Win
removed.description: Finn & Jake challenge a giant monster - "The Farm" - to a fight...but they end up fighting each other!

removed.title: Hitman
removed.description: The Ice King tries to win Princess Bubblegum over with his love potion.

removed.title: Mama Said
removed.description: When King of Ooo sends Finn and Jake on a mission to catch flying mushrooms, they find their loyalty tested.

removed.title: Whispers
removed.description: While safeguarding a frightened Sweet P, Finn is led into a confrontation with an old foe.

removed.title: Storytelling
removed.description: When Jake becomes sick, the only thing that can cure him is a good story, so he asks Finn to go out and find one. The story must have excitement, romance, suspense and, of course, a happy ending. But when nothing interesting happens, Finn tries to make the story happen, accidentally turning the forest animals against each other...and him!

removed.title: Ring of Fire
removed.description: When an old flame comes calling on urgent business, Tree Trunks reconsiders both her wild past and her tranquil present.

removed.title: Vault of Bones
removed.description: Finn's worried that Flame Princess still has evil tendencies in her and wants to shift her alignment to good.

removed.title: I Am a Sword
removed.description: Finn starts having guilt nightmares about his missing Finn Sword but are the nightmares real?
